From: ShellENV Project <shellenv@local>
Subject: [PATCH] closem: do not close TCSH_XTRACEFD

tcsh's closem() closes every fd except SHIN/SHOUT/SHDIAG/OLDSTD/FSHTTY.
That runs early in startup and was closing the fd passed via
TCSH_XTRACEFD, so xtrace/sourcetrace never reached the parent.

Apply after tcsh-TCSH_XTRACEFD.patch.

---
 sh.misc.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/sh.misc.c b/sh.misc.c
index df206c8..1c79d19 100644
--- a/sh.misc.c
+++ b/sh.misc.c
@@ -271,6 +271,7 @@ closem(void)
     for (f = 0; f < num_files; f++)
 	if (f != SHIN && f != SHOUT && f != SHDIAG && f != OLDSTD &&
 	    f != FSHTTY
+	    && (tcsh_xtracefd < 0 || f != tcsh_xtracefd)
 #ifdef MALLOC_TRACE
 	    && f != 25
 #endif /* MALLOC_TRACE */
